Integers anf float

Itâ€™s important to keep in mind that when doing arithmetic with two integers in Ruby, the result will always be an integer.

17 / 5    #=> 3, not 3.4

To obtain an accurate answer, just replace one of the integers in the expression with a float.

17 / 5.0  #=> 3.4



